The agent failed to normalize the participants' "culture" values to the required nationality adjectives ("Vietnamese," "British," "Spanish"), instead echoing country names ("Vietnam," "UK," "Spain"); this mismatch caused the function call not to match the expected format.

The agent incorrectly placed the gear information inside the top-level function call arguments instead of nesting it within hikingDetails.gear as required by the expected function signature, resulting in a parameter structure mismatch.

The agent included an unnecessary period at the end of the "location" value ("123 Main St." instead of "123 Main St"), resulting in a mismatch with the expected function call parameters.

The agent omitted the empty "settings": {} object for the summary widget in the second dashboard, leading to a mismatch with the strict expected function call structure. This structural inaccuracy caused the evaluator to reject the output.
